<section class="applications-section" id="develop-your-own-app">
  <div class="inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Develop your own app</h2>
    <article class="source-article selected">
      <header>
        <h3>The resources on this page provide developers with the tools and information needed to create their own applications that harness Global Forest Watch data.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="content">
        <ul class="faq-list">
          <li>
            <h3>Public API</h3>
            <p>The Global Forest Watch public API is currently in beta. It supports accessing forest change measures of tree cover loss, tree cover gain, and forest disturbance. The following forest change data are now available through the API:
            <ul class='bullets'>
              <li>University of Maryland/Google tree cover loss & gain</li>
              <li>FORMA tree clearing alerts</li>
              <li>IMAZON SAD alerts</li>
              <li>QUICC alerts</li>
              <li>Terra-i alerts</li>
              <li>NASA active fires</li>
            </ul>
            </p>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="https://github.com/wri/gfw-api" target="_blank">API Repository</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Code</h3>
            <p>The Global Forest Watch website and public API are both collaborative and open-source projects hosted on GitHub. If you would like to access or contribute to our source code, please visit GFW on GitHub using the button below where you can send pull requests to our website repository or API repository. All Global Forest Watch source code is released under The MIT License (MIT).</p>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="https://github.com/Vizzuality/gfw">Website Repository</a>
          </li>
            <li>
              <h3>Coming soon</h3>
              <ul class='bullets'>
                <li><strong>Client libraries</strong> for accessing the Global Forest Watch API from JavaScript and Python</li>
                <li><strong>Style guide</strong> for branding Global Forest Watch applications and tools</li>
                <li><strong>The Seed Fund</strong> for supporting developers to build applications using Global Forest Watch data</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Useful links</h3>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="/applications">View existing applications</a>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="https://earthengine.google.org/" target="_blank">Google Earth Engine</a>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="#">ESRI's api info</a>
            <a class="btn gray uppercase medium" href="mailto:datalab@wri.org">App Development Support</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
     </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

